text:
new delhi: gerakan #metoo yang merupakan kampanye terhadap kasus pelecehan seksual tengah ramai di india. banyak selebriti yang akhirnya ikut angkat bicara.

salah satunya jasmin bhasin. aktris┬аdil se dil tak┬аini mengungkap dirinya pernah mengalami pelecehan seksual lima tahun lalu ketika masih menjadi model. тАЬpihak agensi memberi tahu bahwa director ini, yang dikenal atas film gujarati dan hindi-nya, mengadakan audisi untuk film berikutnya. pertemuannya sudah direncanakan, aku lalu bertemu dengannya. aku merasa ada yang salah dari caranya bicara,тАЭ tutur jasmin bhasin, dilansir dari┬аindia-forums, sabtu (20/10/2018). pertanyaan pertama dari sang casting director juga cukup membuat jasmin merasa canggung. тАЬdia tanya, тАШapa yang akan kamu lakukan untuk menjadi seorang aktris dan sejauh mana kamu akan melakukannya?тАЩ karena naif pada waktu itu, aku jawab тАШapa lagi yang bisa saya lakukan, saya meninggalkan kota dan rumah saya dan saya tinggal di sini dan berjuangтАЩтАж aku sadar aku nggak ngerti apa yang dia coba katakan,тАЭ jelasnya.

selanjutnya, sang casting director memintanya untuk melepas pakaian, sehingga dia bisa menilai seperti apa jasmin jika memakai bikini. тАЬdi kasus ini, kau tahu kau tak bisa melawan. jadi aku bilang, aku tidak dalam kondisi bagus untuk memakai bikini. lalu aku diberi briefing, bahwa karakter gadis yang kumainkan itu sangat berbeda dan aku tak perlu pakai bikini. aku segera pergi, agensi akan kembali menemuinya dan aku akan bertemu dengannya lagi,тАЭ kata jasmin. тАЬpelecehan seksual itu tidak dapat disangkal. tapi kita harus kuat. anak perempuan harus tahu cara bekerja dalam kondisi mereka sendiri dan tidak mempercayai siapa pun yang tidak dikenal, ini sangat mudah. penting untuk menjadi pemberani. ini adalah waktu yang tepat untuk mengambil sikap dan aku senang ini terjadi,тАЭ tutupnya. .
.
source by : miyaa

stop_filter_tweet: new delhi : gerakan yang merupakan kampanye terhadap kasus pelecehan seksual tengah ramai di india . banyak selebriti yang akhirnya ikut angkat bicara . salah satunya jasmin bhasin . aktris dil se dil tak ini mengungkap dirinya pernah mengalami pelecehan seksual lima tahun lalu ketika masih menjadi model . тАЬ pihak agensi memberi tahu bahwa director ini , yang dikenal atas film gujarati dan hindi-nya , mengadakan audisi untuk film berikutnya . peemuannya sudah direncanakan , aku lalu beemu dengannya . aku merasa ada yang salah dari caranya bicara , тАЭ tutur jasmin bhasin , dilansir dari india-forums , sabtu ( 20/10/2018 ) . peanyaan peama dari sang casting director juga cukup membuat jasmin merasa canggung . тАЬ dia tanya , тАШ apa yang akan kamu lakukan untuk menjadi seorang aktris dan sejauh mana kamu akan melakukannya ? тАЩ karena naif pada waktu itu , aku jawab тАШ apa lagi yang bisa saya lakukan , saya meninggalkan kota dan rumah saya dan saya tinggal di sini dan berjuang тАЩ тАж aku sadar aku nggak ngei apa yang dia coba katakan , тАЭ jelasnya . selanjutnya , sang casting director memintanya untuk melepas pakaian , sehingga dia bisa menilai sepei apa jasmin jika memakai bikini . тАЬ di kasus ini , kau tahu kau tak bisa melawan . jadi aku bilang , aku tidak dalam kondisi bagus untuk memakai bikini . lalu aku diberi briefing , bahwa karakter gadis yang kumainkan itu sangat berbeda dan aku tak perlu pakai bikini . aku segera pergi , agensi akan kembali menemuinya dan aku akan beemu dengannya lagi , тАЭ kata jasmin . тАЬ pelecehan seksual itu tidak dapat disangkal . tapi kita harus kuat . anak perempuan harus tahu cara bekerja dalam kondisi mereka sendiri dan tidak mempercayai siapa pun yang tidak dikenal , ini sangat mudah . penting untuk menjadi pemberani . ini adalah waktu yang tepat untuk mengambil sikap dan aku seg ini terjadi , тАЭ tutupnya . . . source : miyaa . . follow : . .

i pray that our world is changing... that our society is awakening. so that when, or if, i have daughters one day, they won't feel the need to hold their breath with their keys strategically interwoven in-between their fingers as they walk to their car at night. so that they won't have to text at least two people the details of their first date, "just in case." so that they won't have to keep their eyes and hand glued to the top of their cocktail because they've heard countless accounts of girls getting roofied at bars and parties. so that they won't feel restricted to only running in daylight where people (aka. witnesses) are plentiful. so that they won't deliberately try to make a "resting bitch face" after getting catcalled in an attempt to look as unapproachable as possible; so that they won't silently wonder if they'll get attacked if they clapback. so that they won't question if anyone will even believe them if they say they've been assaulted (god forbid) because "what were you wearing? how much did you drink? were you flirting?"...

text: i will continue to walk purse first through the crowds. i will continue to be a strong, opinionated, self-made gay man. not even those that are suppose to be the closest to us, our families, can keep me from living my truth. turn your back on what is right for your own selfish needs of never knowing a world outside of hancock county. turn your blind eyes away from sexual abuse, never believing the victim and praising the accused. the definition of insanity is doing the same thing over and over again and expecting a different result. i am done living in the insanity and cast you out of my life. society gives us a preconceived idea of how, what, who and why we are alive, and when someoneтАЩs life doesnтАЩt fit that тАЬplanтАЭ society doesnтАЩt know what to with us because how can we be what they havenot told us we could be or do what they have deemed undone? believe women and believe men. our stories are real and our pain is unmeasurable. we forgive but forgiveness does not remove the years of inadequacy, fear and disgust we live with. forgiveness allows us to move on, it does not give you the right to think you enter back into our lives where we left off. your small ways of thinking blind you to what the world really is and your world is defined by county lines, never knowing the beauty, diversity and wonder the world truly has to offer. keep protecting the victims to nurture your own insecurities, but do not be saddened when youтАЩre left alone. itтАЩs the choice youтАЩve made. believe women and believe men. believe children and believe your families. the only person you have to blame for not believing is yourself.  #believesurvivors #iamasurvivor #drford #pursefirst #iaintsorry #youllgetyours #byebitch #mybestlife #metoo

abusive men are born.

many also become abusive by the way they are raised based on the circumstances surrounding their birth.

what do you know about how the man you're dating especially his upbringing and the kind of family he's from? finding answers to these questions may actually be in your best interest. just just fall over heels in love girl... use your head.

text:
(tw: mentions of rape, sexism, et cetera... think: am i really comfortable reading about this? if the answer is no, read with caution!) .
.

consent is a factor in every relationship. friendships, romantic/sexual relationships, even family relationships, all revolve around one thing тАФ consent.
.
.
.

how does consent revolve around our relationships? relationships are strengthened by consent, and allow us a deeper perspective of the relationship; where you stand as an individual and where you and your relation stand as a unity.
.
.
.

let's say your friend asked to borrow a pencil тАФ you'll either say yes or no, or ask then to return it later. this is a form of consent. or, if we were to dive deeper, you might ask for a hug (or imply by opening your arms), and your friend would either say yes or no, or open their arms as well.
.
.
.

in a romantic relationship, asking your partner if you may engage in a polyamorous relationship with another party is a form of asking for consent. your partner may pull you close, and wait for you to either continue contact, or pull away if you're uncomfortable. the same concept goes for sexual relationships.
.
.
.

verbal and non-verbal cues make up what consent really is, yes or no to put it in the most simple way. again, consent is not always verbalтАФbut if you're unsure, ask for verbal affirmation!
.
.
.

is asking for consent only required by males?
no! even if you're a female, you can rape someone. no matter your gender, or lack of it, it does not exclude you from needing consent. it doesn't matter who you are, you must have consent in some shape or form!
.
.
.

can minors give consent?
technically, yes. however, people under the age of 16 don't have fully developed thinking skills, and often they don't fully understand the situation, and that is why they can't give proper consent.
.
.
.

what if my partner makes fun of me/shames me for my body choices?
don't let anyone tell you what to do with your body. everything that happens to your body is your choice only. тАУЁЯЦд
.
.
.

#metoo #femenist #femenism #malebodypositivity #femalebodypositivity #selflove #lgbt #blacklivesmatter #consent

text:
i was 7 when maa was on death bed. her face turned pale yellow and her hair were all gone. i didn't knew back then what breast cancer meant. but i overheard my aunt that maa was at last stage and soon she will visit god's home.

i still remember our last conversation and how she caressed my hair lovingly.
.
"i will turn into a star, do watch me from the earth and i will wave you from the sky." she stated.
.
"i don't want you to go." i cried holding her hand.

and admist the pain and anguish she smiled, proving the warrior she was and exclaimed in a low tone.
.
"everyone has to go beta."
. 
i had no clue what can i do to make her stay.
.
"i will miss you." i cried again.

she, removed her nose ring made of gold and pressed it against my palm.
.
"this is the last thing i can give you, make sure you make the best of its use." and she closed her eyes.

i was 20, and had only 2 things by my side. one, the girl i loved and other the nose ring maa gave. i used to keep it in my wallet as i felt it radiated positivity.

one evening she came crying. i knew her abbu was in hospital. but this time it was serious.
.
"they can't operate until we make the payment." she exclaimed, while tears rolled down her cheeks.
.
"we will manage something." i assured her.

next day, the operation went successful.

that night i went on the terrace and waved.
the star shined brighter.

maybe, mom knew i was going to miss her nose ring.
.
.
darshan sanghvi.
(@darshansanghvi28)
.
.
.

text:
what is self-esteem?  self-esteem concerns the values, beliefs, feelings, thoughts and attitudes we hold in relation to ourselves. it is closely linked to our sense of contentment and fulfillment and  reflects in the way we treat ourselves and how we allow others to treat us. when you are depressed you may believe that you are worthless and treat yourself as though this were true. the more severe the depression, the more powerful this message may become. a survey by dr aaron beck revealed that over 80% of depressed patients expressed thoughts of self-dislike. 
many people define their self-worth by things they have achieved, for example, in the career or hobbies. but being a good squash player or earning a lot of money just means that you are good at square or you earn a lot of money it doesnтАЩt make you a better person. making your self-worth depend on what you achieve can make you feel very pressured,  as you constantly focus on needing to have bigger and bigger achievement in order to feel worthwhile. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2018/10/23/what-is-self-esteem/ #youwillbearwitness #stopchildabuse #stopbullying #stopracism #ptsdawareness #cardinalpell #ptsd #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #erinfado #doitfordolly #metoo

positivity comes in many different forms, in the sense that you can be positive about your personality, body, and life choices. 
that's my goal here, to encourage positivity in every aspect. whether you face discrimination having a different skin color, are the victim of stigma and bias, or have been affected by sexism, i want you to know that i stand behind you, and so do many others! .

ф╕НчЯещБУх╛Юф╜ХцЩВщЦЛхзЛя╝МхЬих╛ИхдЪцЬЛхПЛцИЦхо╢х║ншБЪцЬГщГ╜цЬГшБ╜хИ░хо╢щХ╖хАСцИЦщХ╖ш╝йхАСхХПхАЩчЪДчммф╕АхПешй▒цШпя╝ЪуАМхУЗя╝Мф╜ашВеф║Жх╛ИхдЪя╝БуАНя╝ИчД╢х╛Мф╝╕цЙЛцС╕ф╜ачЪДшВЪхнРя╝ЙцИЦуАМхУЗя╝МцАОщ║╝чШжф║Жх╛ИхдЪя╝БуАНя╝Иф╣ЯцШпф╝╕цЙЛцС╕ф╜ачЪДшВЪхнРя╝ЙуАВх░НцЦ╝ф╗ЦхАСф╛Жшккя╝Мх░▒хГПцШпцЙУцЛЫхС╝ф╕АцигуАВхЫачВ║хБЪх╣ХхЙНя╝МцЙАф╗ецЕвцЕвцОехПЧф║ЖщАЩхАЛцЦЗхМЦуАВф╜ЖхЕ╢хпжчДбшлЦхжВф╜Хя╝Мц▓ТцЬЙф║║хХПщБОф╜ащАЩхАЛф╕Ах╣┤шжЛф╕АцмбчЪД auntie цДПшжЛя╝Мф╣Яц▓ТцЬЙф║║хЦЬцнбчДбчлпчлпч╡жцС╕шВЪхнРцИЦшЗЙчЪДуАВцШихдйя╝МцИСчЬЛшжЛф╕Аф╜Н auntieя╝Мх░НшСЧф╕АхАЛцпФш╝ГхЬУц╜дчЪДх░ПцЬЛхПЛ я╝ИхдзцжВ 10 цн▓я╝ЙчЪДхк╜хк╜хдзшБ▓хЬ░шкк я╝Ихе╜хГПщВгх░ПцЬЛхПЛшБ╜ф╕НхИ░ф╕Ацигя╝Йя╝ЪуАМхУЗя╝Бф╜аф╗Фф╗Фхе╜шВечкйя╝БцЙЛшЗВф╗▓ч▓ЧщБОф╜ая╝БшжБц╕ЫшВечкйя╝БуАНя╝ИчД╢х╛Мф╝╕цЙЛцС╕ф╗ЦчЪДшЗЙш╖ЯшВЪхнРя╝ЙуАВцИСчЬЛхИ░щВгхАЛх░ПцЬЛхПЛх╛Ихд▒шР╜я╝МхПкцШпшгЭф╜Ьц▓ТщЧЬф┐ВчЪДч╣╝ч║МчОйчОйхЕ╖уАВх░ПцЬЛхПЛчЪДхк╜хк╜ф╣ЯцДЯшж║х╛Их░╖х░мя╝МчлЛхИ╗цК▒шСЧхЕТхнРшжкф╕АхПгуАВчЬЛхИ░х░ПцЬЛхПЛщВгщ║╝ф╕НщЦЛх┐Гя╝МцИСф╣ЯхШЧшйжх╣лф╗ЦцМ╜хЫЮф╕Ащ╗Юх░КхЪ┤я╝Мшккя╝МуАМф╕НцШпхХКя╝Мф╗ЦщВДцШпщВгщ║╝хПпцДЫхТМщЭЪф╗Фя╝БщВДхНБхИЖцДЫщБЛхЛХя╝Б уАНуАВф║║чФЯцЬЙщВгщ║╝хдЪщЗНшжБчЪДф║Ля╝МчВ║чФЪщ║╝шжБчммф╕АхПех░▒цЙ╣хИдхИеф║║чЪДхдЦшбихСвя╝ЯчВ║чФЪщ║╝ф╕НщЧЬх┐Гф╕Аф╕Лф║║хо╢х╖еф╜Ь/хо╢ф║║/ф╗КхдйщБОх╛ЧщЦЛх┐ГхЧОя╝Я цИСхАСф║║шИЗф║║ф╣ЛщЦУчЪДх░Ншй▒хЛЩх┐ЕшжБщВгщ║╝шЖЪц╖║хЧОя╝Я

food for thought:
don't know when it became socially acceptable for people to start conversations by commenting on weight gain or loss. being in my industry, i get comments all the time about my weight (not saying that's ok either). it's almost like a greeting. however, yesterday, i witnessed an "auntie" commenting on a little kid (around 10 years old) on how fat he was and how big is belly is (and then proceed to touch is belly and cheeks). since when was that a kind gesture or a cute hello? it can be damaging to a kid's self esteem in so many ways. i immediately endeavored to rescue a bit of the kid's shattered dignity by complimenting him on how athletic he was (he was jumping around before). there are better conversation starters than that. shoutout to all of you who have been emotionally abused like that before! stay strong! their opinions don't matter. smile on! ЁЯТк
.
.
.

text:
absolutely love love love "medusa" by @jasminvardimoncompany tonight. two more performances at @sadlers_wells through wednesday. go see the show!!!
.
i was blown away by the company's production of "pinocchio" last year. i've been both excited yet nervous about tonight. will the new work bring the same level of creativity, intensity, playfulness, and stunning technical execution as last year --- especially when the new creation is an abstract concept?
.
medusa surpassed pinocchio at every level.
.
i interpreted the show as centering around men's desire for power, control, and exploitation --- over women, over the environment, and even over mythical creations --- and the resulting damage. the piece is dark and emotional, speaks to current events, and challenges the audience to think twice about the complex, unspoken, or forgotten root cause of the societal issues today.
.
thank you, jasmin and the dancers @jas0rr, @clavelandco, @pattitrash, @andrer15, lucija bo┼╛i─Нevi─З, @silcolibri, @the_._ron, @joshuajs91, for giving us an absolutely incredible experience tonight.
.
memorable scenes.
.
"the housewife" and how men assert psychological, emotional, physical control over women. the girl on stage is a pretty inanimate doll to be dressed up, to be accessorized for men, to be waltzed (and tossed) around by men, until she is eventually transformed into a housewife. even in her adult form, her body is still owned by men --- who extended their arms, reached inside of her vagina as they pleased, and ripped the fetus right out of her as they wished. in the background of the housewife scene are two young women out and about --- trying to enjoy a day at the beach while wearing a gas mask to survive.
.
during the post-show chat, jasmin explained that most people remember only the ending of the greek mythology where medusa is a terrifying monster. however, she was not born that way. medusa was once a beautiful maiden, but was raped by the god of the sea in athena's temple. her later form came from her anger and her rage, yet the early part of her story is often omitted or even forgotten. #metoo #believesurvivors
name: Jason Chuang

the story goes like this
v:

the next day i bought new bedding. expensive. two weeks later i still couldnтАЩt lie still through a night. whenever i felt too comfortable i shifted my back or stretched my legs or reached my arm above my head to cover an ear. i donтАЩt like my ears uncovered. still air even had a way of waking me. too hot. too cold. what was that? the doors are locked itтАЩs nothing. my dog, stella, began sleeping with me again. i didnтАЩt have to invite her. she knew. her breath lulled. i remember her warmth. i should have been smarter.

i smoked cigarettes after work and ate barely any food all day. maybe half a fried egg sandwich. saltines. food tasted off. bile crept up my esophagus to the point where i would exhale and feel close to puking. saliva refilled my mouth on rotation. like a washing machine starting a new load every hour. will this pass? swallow. again, swallow. do take a leave from work? donтАЩt put your life on hold because of him. this will pass. work. breathe. pet stella. call mom. breathe, deeply.

text:
with the angst i feel from disharmony in this world and midterm elections coming up, it has brought to light my struggle to share/not share my history of sexual abuse...i feel compelled to talk about the issues that still affect me today: the main ptsd i have is the fear of reporting (talking) and being believed (trust). i actually did report my biggest perpetrator when i was 10 years old to another close female family member. she grabbed my face in her hand, looked me in the eyes and told me that x loved me and that this abuse i spoke of did not happen. the betrayal and fear i felt in that instance kept me quiet for many years. it continued to perpetuate the feelings of shame, questioning my reality and believing it was my fault. i endured other encounters of abuse and felt helpless to do anything about it. my truth continued to reveal itself in harmful ways. my art and my spirituality have given me a voice to work through most of this and i am eternally grateful for this gift. i will not let fear keep me quiet anymore. i also will believe anyone who tells me they have been sexually abused regardless of their story or how much time has passed. if they are тАЬlyingтАЭ then the universe can judge them, not me. another avenue for using our voices is to vote so please do so. for those of you who continue to deny sexual abuse victims, and are conscious of it, fvck off ЁЯЪл
flyer courtesy of @acehotel 
#findingmyvoice #youhaveavoice #vote #midtermelections #twomoreweeks #truth #karma #ibelieveyou #metoo #poundmetoonotfunny #empowerment #spirituality #healing #ptsd #abuseisnotokay #pushingthroughfear #notmyfault #arttherapy #healingthroughart

text:
when i was 14 years old an amazing group of people came into my life. i didnтАЩt know it then but these people soon became my family. when my biological mother gave me up they, without question took me in and chose to love me as one of their own. years have passed and i have been calling them mom/dad/brother/family all along. 
over the summer my parents decided to go through the process of adult adoption. today we got confirmation from our lawyer. 
my adoption has been processed. i am now officially apart of the family. #adoption #poetsofig  #poetsunite  #poetryisnotdead  #verseoftheday  #poetrylove  #poetofinstagram  #poetrylover #survivor #clickclackding #typewriter #typewriterpoetry #writersofinstagram #writtenart #healing #metoo #writerscommunity #writing #writersofig #writersnetwork #writerscorner #writeyourownstory

text:
тАЬthere was a boy in high school that was part of my group of friends. i'm sure at some point i had a crush on him. but his lack of respect for people's personal space was a reoccurring issue. he even joked that his father didnt hug him enough as a kid. he would lean on me, hug me, even pick me up when i insisted he shouldn't. everyone would laugh, i was small, he was strong. he was always laughing. i couldn't bring myself to use my serious voice with him and assumed that if only i could then he'd understand, but i couldn't. he was in my art class, so was my boyfriend, and one day it became clear that my boyfriend was uncomfortable with all the physical contact. we argued about it and i told him that it was something i couldn't fix, but he didn't seem to understand, i felt hurt. maybe it was wrong of me to assume he'd confront a stranger simply to be "the man defending his woman." maybe it was wrong of me to assume it was anyone else's job to do what i now know i am capable of.тАЭ .
.
.
.
.

text:
in life we experience extreme highs and at the same time we experience some pretty extreme lows. .

life is kind of like one big crazy roller coaster itтАЩs start slowly, it fills you with the anticipation and curiosity takes you up and then sends you flying down only to rise you up again. we laugh, we cry, we experience a few moments where we wanted it all to stop.  but it just keeps going. we end up settling for security, we just want to feel safe.

not recognizing that life has its ups and downs, that being defeated and making a comeback is just as important as moving forward because itтАЩs in those moments that youтАЩre thinking youтАЩve hit the bottom, that youтАЩre only just beginning to cut yourself a new path in life.  you not being defeated youтАЩre being defined!
.

in the journey of life we pass through pleasure and pain. there will be sunshine and rain; theyтАЩll be loss and gain. but we will move forward again and again. donтАЩt judge the moment. donтАЩt hang on because it will keep pushing you forward. .

and remember, this morning if youтАЩre healthy. youтАЩre happier than 1 million people that will not survive this week. if thereтАЩs food in your fridge, shoes on your feet, close on your body, a bed to sleep on, and a roof over your head youтАЩre richer than 75% of the people in this world. .

dr. wayne dryer said it best, тАЬwhen we change the way we look at things, the things we look at change.тАЭ .

i know youтАЩve got another comeback in you! we all do! redefine yourself as the comeback kid! wear it as a badge of honor. you earned it! .
.
.
.

text:
brought my @vitamix and @rising_springs water on my trip to keep my costs down and wellness on track. since i was driving it was easy to pack and tonight i opted to make a quick smoothie rather than eat out. 
it's more fun to me to spend a few nights being more frugal and then splurge on a more fancy dinner towards the weekend. i used to be more frivolous with my money and health when i was drinking, there seemed to always be an excuse for overindulging. now without the alcohol pulling me in i can resist the urge to eat out. it might seem boring but it's not for me. i have travelled so much over the past ten years and know that i am not missing out on anything by not hitting up the bars and lounges. it's much better to be free from the desire to escape

text:
i did used to wish to be free.  on birthday cakes or toasting shots- i would wish to be free. 
have you ever watched a woman seemingly glide across the floor with zero fucks given and notice the ease and grace she carried herself?  the freedom she had to laugh, to dance, to love.

text:
femmes f├йroces // for indian women, the courage to identify a man in power does not come easily. in a culture where sexual harassment is normalised and trivialised, where the line of consent is blurred by the patriarchy and flawed ideas of machismo, where a womenтАЩs testimony is too often disregarded, it took an external force, in the form of #metoo, to call out their alleged tormentors. 
as unsparing this movement has been in our country, it taught us three very important lessons. 
taking a stand for yourself at any point of time is not wrong. women have seen years of misbehaviour and harassment worrying about men in powerful chairs. but that doesnтАЩt give them right to walk over you. speak up! 
listen. please listen to what the victim has to say. being judgemental and insensitive makes you a convict too. 
last but most important, courage. it takes massive courage to accept and narrate your adversity to the society.

text:
hot news
rana daggubati gantikan nana patekar di proyek film housefull 4 ЁЯШЙ

gerakan #metoo memperoleh banyak dukungan dari selebriti bollywood dan banyak tokoh industri terkenal dituduh melakukan pelecehan seksual. efek dari gerakan itu mengarah ke banyak hal seperti sajid khan mundur sebagai sutradara film 'housefull 4' setelah dituduh. aktor kawakan nana patekar juga dikeluarkan dari proyek tersebut karena ia dituduh oleh tanushree dutta. kemudian, farhad samji menggantikan sajid khan dan berita baru-baru ini adalah bahwa nana patekar akan digantikan oleh anil kapoor. 
sekarang menurut laporan, rana daggubati kemungkinan besar yang akan menggantikan nana patekar di 'housefull 4'. laporan media mengatakan bahwa rana baru-baru ini telajh didekati oleh pembuat 'housefull 4' setelah nana patekar keluar dari film di tengah kontroversi #metoo yang sedang berlangsung. namun, kabar tersebut belum ada konfirmasi resmi yang sama.

angsuran keempat dari waralaba komedi hit 'housefull' didasarkan pada tema reinkarnasi. menurut produser sajid nadiadwala, 'housefull 4' akan menjadi film komedi india yang dianggarkan paling tinggi. ini dijadwalkan untuk mencapai layar bioskop pada tahun 2019 selama diwali. 
housefull 4 akan menampilkan akshay kumar, bobby deol, ritesh deshmukh, pooja hedge, kriti sanon dan kriti kharbanda. ЁЯШЙ

text: most people just see a building with windows. i see a major #metoo moment. after 44 years of thinking about this moment, today i visited #bakeruniversity where i spent my freshman semester. bmoc, football/basketball star, senior asked me out. wow, me! after several dates, we went back to his #fraternity house. consensually intimate. i asked about the lights in the window. he said cars going by. in the second floor window? a few days later, i was talk of the campus. "car lights" were camera flashes. he and his brothers conspired to take pix. i left school in disgrace. now, i realize i could have stayed to fight. they were wrong. not me. today was very #cathartic. thanks mr. #bakeruniversity alumni official for listening and apologizing. never again will i let someone have that kind of #control over me. he better never be nominated for the #supremecourt #iwilltalk #metoomovement . today was a very good day in #kansas and #bakeru is a really good school.

text:
+body talk+ 
yes, i am trying very hard to suck in my belly. 
i come from a culture where beauty is extremely narrow. even when i moved to a different culture and thought i was accepted for my difference or тАЬexoticтАЭ looks. i thought my body didnтАЩt truly belonged in a single standard. i was too chubby as a korean. i was not skinny but also not тАЬcurvy тАЬ enough. 
i was sexually assaulted and harassed numerous times since i was young and i never talked about it openly until my 20тАЩs.  i truly hated calling myself тАЬa victimтАЭ. i hated my sexualized body because objectification meant ugly to me.  i had to fake it till i make it to love myself and my body. 
i came so far now. i am slowly falling in love with myself. i had to give myself some love because love from others used to mean nothing to me. feeling pretty and being pretty is a totally different thing. and with social media nowadays a lot of people are feeling less pretty. it is hard sometimes but learn not to compare yourself to others. there is only one,  you  in this world and you only get one life. so love yourself as hard you can. love yourself so much that you look in the mirror and say тАЬ damnnn that bitch is looking fine afтАЭ. love yourself so much that you would rather enjoy your own company than going out sometimes. give yourself somee goooooddd lovin ladies and gentlemen because you deserve it тЩея╕П #bodypositivity #metoo #metoomovement #bodyimage #bodyimagemovement

ЁЯФК #betofortexas тАФ#donaldtrump on monday unveiled a new nickname for republican sen. #tedcruz, showcasing how much their relationship has shifted since the 2016 presidential campaign.
-
trump told reporters cruz is no longer "lyin' ted," instead, he called him "beautiful ted." donald trump on monday unveiled a new nickname for republican sen. ted cruz, showcasing how much their relationship has shifted since the 2016 presidential campaign.
-
#trump also said he doesn't "regret" suggesting cruz's father was involved in the assassination effort of president john f. kennedy, which was among his more controversial statements regarding the #texas senator as they both vied for the gop presidential nomination.
-
"i don't regret anything, honestly," "it all worked out very nicely." trump said
-
in may 2016, trump said to fox news: "[cruz's] father was with lee harvey oswald prior to oswald's being тАФ you know, shot. i mean, the whole thing is ridiculous. what is this, right prior to his being shot, and nobody even brings it up. they don't even talk about that. that was reported, and nobody talks about it."
-
"i mean, what was he doing тАФ what was he doing with lee harvey oswald shortly before the death? before the shooting?" trump added at the time. "it's horrible." -
during his 2016 presidential campaign, trump also attacked the appearance of cruz's wife. but the president said he and cruz have since buried the hatchet and that he now likes his former opponent.
-
this all comes as trump endorses cruz ahead of november's midterm elections. he's set to appear alongside cruz at a rally in houston on monday night to urge voters to support him.
-
cruz has faced a tough race against democratic rep. #betoorourke, who's fighting to unseat the texas senator. trump on monday told reporters he thinks o'rourke is "highly overrated."

тАЬwe are the untamed. 
we are the unashamed.
we are beautiful justice. 
just watch us rise.тАЭ ЁЯФе

today, by the pacific ocean, i finished the final edit for my memoir тАЬbeautiful justiceтАЭ, the story of how i reclaimed my worth and creative power after sex trafficking, rape and domestic violence. this book is also a celebration of the women and girls who shared their sacred stories with me and invited me to be a part of their healing path. it is my soul medicine and love letter for survivors who are becoming leaders. together we are making this world a more just and compassionate place. ЁЯФе

in april 2019 #beautifuljustice will be coming your way through @sealpress and @hachettebooks and i am thrilled to share what i learned about creating my own justice after trauma. i hope you will join the conversation and share what #beautifuljustice means to you. 
in fierce love, 
brooke (photo by the exquisite @briophoto)

text:
тЬзcomplex ptsd criteria: part 1тЬз
now that we've done a brief overview on how complex ptsd differs from ptsd, we'd like to take a much deeper look into individualized criteria for c-ptsd - how the condition truly manifests into one's entire world and self-view, beyond just the posttraumatic symptoms.
.
the first of these criteria is "alternations in emotion regulation". emotions are challenging for many people, but they are especially difficult for those who've survived complex trauma. for most, showing emotions wasn't safe. survivors were sent mixed messages and given different responses, often violent ones, for each display of emotion. just as things seemed predictable, they would change. what was allowed one day wasn't tolerated the next. now, as an adult, re-experiencing traumatic content, including dissociated emotions, via flashbacks and intrusive symptoms can take this familiar challenge to the next level. survivors may feel their emotions are unpredictable, all-consuming, and either come at full speed or endless lulls of numbness or apathy.
.
luckily, there are great coping skills that make emotion regulation much more feasible (there's even an entire category of dbt dedicated to it)! we deeply empathize with all of you who are struggling to just understand or name your feelings, let alone feel them and then navigate them gracefully! we send you our utmost compassion, with a promise that it can get better.
.
stay tuned for our next posts as we discuss the rest!
.
ЁЯТЬЁЯТЩЁЯТЫ
.
[as a note: c-ptsd is still not formally recognized in the dsm, but these criteria have existed and been used by practitioners for awhile despite the lack of a diagnostic code.]
.
.
.
.
.

text:
#respectmetoo is encouraging consensual, safe, equal and respectful relationships free from sexual violence. 
there are some people who think that feminism and the need to highlight womenтАЩs rights is no longer necessary. unfortunately the statistics regarding womenтАЩs exposure to sexual violence and other gender based violence paints a very different picture. we should all wish for a society where people feel safe to live their lives without violence. respecting each other is a good place to start. 
#sexualviolenceawarenessmonth #respect #metoo #betterworld #equality #qsan #queenslandsexualassaultnetwork #sexualassault

text:
this isn't going to be a regular post... this isn't going to be a photoshopped, filtered image of myself. recently i've been looking in the mirror and not liking what i see physically. it is no surprise that during my time at university i have gained a significant amount of weight due to unhealthy eating, not taking care of myself and lack of motivation; which has led to some very negative and abusive thoughts about myself. however i do strongly believe in body positity and that every body is beautiful but i know that my relationship with food is unhealthy and that i eat to numb alot of pain and feelings that i've been experiencing, nd that when i look at myself i don't like what i see, this is not soully influenced by perfected images from social media (although that does have a big part to do with it) but looking at the damage i have done to myself in masking alot of pain. i was focusing so much on my relationships with other who didn't have the best interest for me than caring for myself, i untag myself from images i find repulsive of me and photoshop and edit them to a version of me that i'd be happier as... however life isn't photoshopped and u can't put filters through people's eyes in person... i'm trying to work on myself mentally, emotionally and physically, and a little reminder to say that just because your not happy with urself doesn't mean you can't change it, but realistically it won't happen overnight or a week... so i believe in you on whatever journey your on.
~
~
ik this is a bit of a ramble, nd most of you won't care but i put this as a message really to myself to really continue with the change i have started
#mentalhealth #clean #cleaneating #body #bodypositve #bodypositivity #itsokaynottobeokay #metoo #fat #joruney #body #fitnessjourney #betterself #selfimprovment

text:
self love is a big thing for me now. i never had any love for myself or respect for that matter. i always tried to please people & that was took for granted, from friends aswell as an ex. i wasnt appreciated which then led me into an abusive relationship ЁЯТФ
.
my ex knew my flaws & weaknesses & used that against me. he didn't try to help me or encourage me, he turned that into his twisted game to try & destroy me ЁЯШб
.
it might have damaged me for 3.5yrs, but he didn't succeed in destroying me. thanks to him, the police arrived at my door & saved me from any more of his abuse. the law may have failed me, for now, but that day & weeks after, the police helped me through so much. i am thankful for 2 things that day.....the police & my eyes being opened to how much i didn't love myself. now i make it a point to love myself & not give 2 shits about who likes me & who doesn't. i'm me & my past has made me who i am.....and im still standing!! you can stand too ЁЯТЬ
.

text:
тШЭя╕Пnew postтШЭя╕П the ugly #metoo truth of #solofemaletravel
тЭд
tw: sexual assault
тЭд
a few months ago, @sempiterna_ dmed me about writing an essay on the lack of discussion in the travel world regarding sexual assault and her own experiences with sexual assault while traveling. when i read her first draft, i felt so many of my own experiences were validated. truly, every woman who travels has probably experienced things like this. as letitia points out in her essay, it's not that assault happens more while we're traveling, it's that we're far away from our support systems and less equipped to deal with the aftermath. that is why it's so important that we have this conversation in the travelsphere.
тЭд
if you don't know who @sempiterna_ is by now, you should. the first thing you'll notice is probably her incredible sense of style, but as soon as you start scrolling through her captions, you'll learn that she's also a fantastic writer with a fun, unique, honest, and compassionate personality. she embodies what it means to learn from and empower each other. i'm deeply honored to have provided a home for this essay, and i hope you will all get as much from it as i did. if you could leave a comment of support after reading, that would be wonderful. anything even remotely unsupportive will be removed.
тЭд
i also want to thank letitia and every other person out there who has spoken up about sexual assault. you all are my idols. if you've spoken up, know that it's not in vain, and if you haven't, know that that's okay too, and not being ready doesn't make you weak. surviving makes you strong. it's not your fault.
тЭд

text:
op-ed: he asked me to тАЬplay doctorтАЭ
-
evalaurene r. jean-charles is a ronald e. mcnair scholar, vera fellow, secretary of the john jay black students union, and is in the john jay honors program
-
he caressed her lower back in a way that was all too familiar. with every sweep of his finger, i felt shivers swimming down my spine. fear overwhelmed me. i feared for her. i feared his touch would leave her with the same insecurity that still, years later, lives in me. i feared he would make her play doctor, just as he made me years before.
-
the cameras have stopped rolling and the headlines have moved on but as a sexual assault survivor, the pain associated with the appointment of judge brett kavanaugh remains. the fact that disclosing can be the hardest part for men and women who have been victims of this sort of violence remains.
-
my story, like dr. fordтАЩs, comes with torment and hesitation, self-doubt, and self-hate. i didnтАЩt want to tell my story, and still to this day i donтАЩt know if i would have until i saw him pruning a young girl i love. there he was, laughing and showing her videos. i wouldnтАЩt have been able to live with myself if that little girl had to face his abuse. i didnтАЩt want her to constantly fear what lurked in the dark, or re-learn how to trust any man trying to love her.
-
i can see how professor ford grappled with the decision to tell anyone what happened to her, but when she saw the man who she believes to have attacked her being nominated to sit on the highest court of the land, i believe her when she says the memories all came rushing back.
-
when i look back at my younger self, i realize my stepbrother touching me is one of my first and most vivid memories and every day i wish i could erase them. the tears in my fatherтАЩs eyes, the anger and shame i saw on my motherтАЩs face while i was forced to recount those fresh memories of what he did over and over. i was forced to tell strangers how he asked me to тАЬplay doctorтАЭ not knowing what that meant and how he promised to put his hands in my pants to make me тАЬfeel good,тАЭ if i did it to him first. i had to tell them how he forced himself into my mouth and how he used the red bottle of

of the future generations, restore balance and vote blue. i understand it's sad for you to think of a world without you, or outside of yourself, but this is too important. if it's your relationship with god and heaven, do you want to look from heaven to see the damage of sandy mists, no topsoil, no time to teach or learn for any color, and hazards beyond anyone at that point. this is the time and place to defend our water, our livelihood as well as all the other lifeforms, including representing everyone with thumbs as an equal part of the human race. we may or may not be on sacred land. depends on who you represent i suppose, regardless, where i'm standing, is rather important to me. have enough respect for yourselves to acknowledge, we may not have all the answers, not everything is perfect or discovered, yet it's pretty cool to be standing on this floating space rock, and all forms of life past, present and future are welcome to the experience, and no human has any place to text:
this morning, i got an email from an online fitness personality called "9 fitness questions i'm confused about."
.
it was meant to be funny. but i wasn't laughing when i read: "why do some girls show up damn near naked to work out and then complain about getting too much attention? nice try."
.
guys, i couldn't hit unfollow fast enough.
.
this is not a joke. this is a problem. whatever your political views are, it's a problem when men see clothing as an invitation, or a get out of jail free card. even if they're only laughing about it.
.
i've personally gotten tons of 100% unwanted attention in the gym. i'm often one of few women in a weight room full of guys, and i'm aware that i stand out.
.
and yes, i wear tank tops and leggings, because i'm working out and it's comfortable and i like it, but i assure you that i'm far from naked.
.
and is it not possible that i could wear that and still legitimately not want any attention? could i maybe wear that and still deserve to be left alone?
.
i understand that there are decent men who misunderstand women's cues, and there are women who are sensitive (yes, #metoo). i don't think anyone can deny that there's a deep, complex social issue here, which can't be fixed with a simple set of rules.
.
all i'd like to say is that when it comes to the gym, specifically, women need to feel safe and comfortable.
.
the gym is already such a vulnerable place, in so many different ways. and there are a lot of people who are in there because of insecurities, so there is certainly no need to pile on more.
.
this is just one of the many reasons i'm so excited to be opening a women's gym.
.
sometimes, i think, women just need their own space.
.
that's all.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#lionessfitness #wearewomen #hearusroar
name: Lioness Fitness

.

.

.

.

.

.

text:
when i was a teenager up through my early 20's, i wanted to take my life. 
many times, i attempted, and not one time did i think i had more reason to stay here than to leave. if anything, i just desperately did not want to be here anymore.
.
i was completely broken trying to navigate life. i searched for love in all the wrong places, only to feel anything other than that, which spiraled me down farther into a path of destructiveness. i was in a household filled with anger, mental, emotional (and sometimes physical) abuse and that led me even further in a belief that i had zero reason to be on this planet. i had zero self-worth, and it was evident in my actions.
.
i drank a lot and did many drugs to escape the pain. which became an ugly cycle as well and also put the two hand in hand perfectly. most people dealing with mental health problems are also dealing with substance abuse problems, and it's likely because they are trying to escape their reality, no matter the way.
.
the unfortunate part of all of it, is that the substance abuse usually leads to them only hurting themselves and others around them, which causes even more isolation and pain for them, leaving the cycle to essentially spiral out of control if something doesn't change.
.
you guys, mental health matters. you couldn't ask me to take my life today, and i couldn't imagine it. you couldn't pay me, you couldn't coerce me, you'd have to take my life yourself, before i would. it took me a long time to get to this point in my life, and when things that i stuffed in a box and shoved away to hope to never deal with again, pop up, it's hard not to go back to that place and cry for myself, remembering the pain i was once fighting through.
.
it wasn't until i was actually admitted into a mental health facility that i received some of the most crucial help i needed. they had me perform exercises that would help me cope in a constructive way rather than destructive.
.
it's funny, you know. i have never had an issue saying out loud, i was in a mental institution. 
i think people think you're crazy. it's like they imagine you in this padded room, tied up, losing your mind. (more in comments)

text:
for 8 years my primary and most honest form of expression has been improvising.

any overwhelming feeling leads me to sit at a piano and just see what will come out. 
i never share this material, even with friends. partly because i donтАЩt have good quality equipment to record but mostly because this is the most vulnerable, honest and sometimes absolutely crazy that you will ever see. 
the last few days iтАЩve found myself in 30/40 minute long improvs... mostly about rape. 
and i thought... people need to see this... because it is no joke. gonna be posting 5-6 videos of this improv i did today. expect candid, crazy, angry and downright unapologetic truth. 
this one touches partly on the common тАЬyou asked for itтАЭ, which so many survivors are hit with. frankly, what a load of shit. 
peace out & ps. donтАЩt be a rapist. thanks.

text:
*warning* this book is about sexual assault and could be triggering for some.)
~r e v i e w~
we believe you: survivors of campus sexual assults speak out
by annie e. clark and andrea l. pino
368 pages
@henryholtbooks
(this is an older title)
тАв
"being a survivor is being part of a club that nobody wants to join. but once you're in it you're in it for life. and it's the strongest group of people you could ever imagine."
-julia d.
тАв
this was a hard read. the subject matter isnt light. it is about sexual assaults on campus. in this book students from all different colleges and universities,  public and private share their experiences of trauma and healing and activism. these stories are told from students of different races, different family backgrounds,  it's very diverse and a very very hard read.

a book of this subject matter i honestly can't rate in a matter of stars. it was a good read but a hard read. the student stories we're so vivid. this would be a very hard read for anybody that's been through any kind of sexual assault. 
i appreciate these student telling their stories because i think books like this are important. and if you can handle it they are definitely worth reading.
тАв 
thank you to the publisher for sending it to me. .
.
.

.

once again, the #trumpadministration is coming after #birthcontrol. specifically, they are looking to issue rules that would roll back the affordable care act mandate that requires that most employers provide insurance that covers it, which would leave god knows how many women across the country without access. trump had previously attempted to eliminate this mandate last year, but said attempt was┬аblocked by two federal judges┬аon the grounds that doing so would cause "serious and irreparable harm.".
.
but now┬аthey're trying again, because forcing people to have unwanted children just seems like a really fantastic time to them, i guess.
.

these new rules would allow any employer to refuse to provide their employees with insurance that covers birth control if they object to doing so not only for religious reasons, but for "sincerely held" moral beliefs. like spite.
the trump administration, naturally, is pushing the idea that this is an issue of "religious freedom." it is not.
.  if health insurance that covers birth control were somehow more expensive than insurance that does not, they might have an argument. it is not.
.
 it costs the exact same amount. there is no special discount given on plans that do not provide birth control coverage either. so really, it's about employers wanting to have more control over the sexual activities of their employees. it's about believing that you ought to have the "#religiousfreedom" to force your employees to follow the tenets of your religion whether they believe in it or not.
.
but much as this is an attack on women, it's not just a #womansrights issue. it's also a labor issue, and a pretty serious one at that.
employer-based health insurance is part of an employee's compensation. just as an employer should not be allowed to tell an employee what to spend their paycheck on, they should not be allowed to determine what they can use their health insurance for. it should be as simple as that.

text:
#la tonight! #trans panel:
join us on monday october 22, 2018 for this important conversation. 
doors will open at 7pm and panel will start at 7:30pm
#metoo #metoosurvivorsmarch #translivesmatter #metoomovement

join us and bring a friend to our fourth panel in a 6-panel series in the lead up to our me too survivors march on november 10, 2018

me too march international  intends to help amplify the experiences of those who have been affected by sexual assault and harassment, but often, lgbtq people go unnoticed, especially transgender people. itтАЩs important to acknowledge that sexual violence, misconduct, and mistreatment is an urgent issue among the community that many transgender people experience.

trans people face sexual violence and harassment at alarmingly high rates. as reported in the 2015 u.s. trans survey, nearly half (47%) of respondents had been sexually assaulted at some point in their lifetime.

these already devastating numbers were higher among people of color. american indian, multiracial, middle eastern, and black respondents were most likely to have been sexually assaulted in their lifetime. these rates were also higher among specific communities such as undocumented trans people and those with disabilities.

trans people who are more vulnerable experience high levels of poverty, unemployment, homelessness, job and housing insecurity, and incarceration. these compounding factors often force trans people of color, undocumented trans people, and disabled trans people into circumstances that put their safety at risk and make them more susceptible to sexual assault.

text:
the courageous and beautiful soul - tess mix.
.
tess is 32 years of young, dwelling in brooklyn ny. "i have been documenting the spirits and bar industry for 8 years, but if i wasnтАЩt doing this, i would be a masseuseтАЭ, says tess on her profession. when asked about changes coming in the next several years, "i want to see more green bartending. more recycling, more composting. i want that for the world. i would also like to see more interesting secondary spirits for bartenders so we can see more diverse cocktails." shoulda, woulda, coulda - тАЬhindsightтАЭ is a powerful concept, with that in mind, tess advises her 16-year-old self, тАЬit gets better. i promise.тАЭ tess has a lot to say, sheтАЩs an advocate and an activist. sitting down with anyone тАУ living or deceased for a good conversation, she says, тАЬi can't hide from the political. i want open conversation; and by тАШopenтАЩ i would think possibly confrontational in some way. i would like to talk to robert mueller and ask him what there is in this investigation. i want to know what is wrong with the usa.тАЭ on the topic of travel, tess says, тАЬi would love to visit newfoundland. it seems like the land of my dreams: the northeast, cold, calm and solitary. i would like to think i would find some kind of peace.тАЭ on her pefect day, her sweetest moments can be spent at hartley's тАУ tessтАЩ local тАУ on sunday afternoon with a cider, her dog and a book. after a pint, her twinny (the equally fierce and incredible) ivy mix would should up with claire sprouse and they would while away the day. when i asked tess, if she could describe herself in one word or one sentence, she said тАЬi'm made of steel, if you don't look close enough.тАЭ #minibarleadingladies

in discussion with @zoomtv about abuse of power, and what it means. why women donтАЩt speak up, and why we as a society judge women for doing what they do, even though we do not judge the men abusing their power. ask yourself how often you look at a new actress and say тАШshe mustтАЩve fucked her way on topтАЩ, but at the same time, we donтАЩt look at the men that are casting them and say тАШi wonder how often he has abused his power to misuse them.тАЩ she does it even though she shouldnтАЩt have to, and you slut shame her. 
he does it, and you say тАШso many sluts are ready to give inтАЩ
really?
the same logic applies when we talk about physical or sexual abuse towards women all over our society. we judge the victim, we dissect her character, we refuse to believe her story. 
for those that are still confused, #metoo is about about work place assault, it is also about psychical and sexual abuse in relationships. me too is about a womanтАЩs right to be treated equally. the campaign started by people in media to bring sexism in the industry to lime light - but that doesnтАЩt mean its limited to work places. 
me too, is about empowering women.

text:
i just made two payments on never-ending medical bills.
.
i worried about how we would manage financially if i became a sahm. we donтАЩt struggle by any stretch however - we built a life around 2 full-time incomes with benefits. so naturally things became tighter when we cut one of those out plus the expense of insurance.
.
i started my virtual fitness business first as someone wanting to become healthier and stronger as a new mom while i was still working full time. i am so glad i did. unexpected expenses are always going to pop up and while i didnтАЩt have to have a side hustle while staying home i wanted to.
.
itтАЩs in my nature to want to contribute financially and how daggon freeing is it to be working for myself, on my own schedule, getting into the best shape ever and put away money every week for the unexpected. give ourselves some wiggle room for playing. permission to enroll my daughter in dance. relax about getting my hair done. continue sending her to a great preschool a few days a week.
.
i know it can seem like тАЬman iтАЩll never be paying my mortgage with any online faux businessтАЭ but...what if it covered groceries that month? your hospital payment? your insurance premium? your weekly starbucks treat? wouldnтАЩt that be worth it? it is to me ЁЯШК
.
you have a real person right тАЬin frontтАЭ of you inviting you to do just that. saying no leaves you right where you are. saying yes has endless possibilitiesтЬМЁЯП╝ЁЯТБЁЯП╝тАНтЩАя╕П

text:
four more days til the daddies comes out and i want to say, wow, it's not for everyone. it's full of #sex and #violence and is meant to be a bit #disturbing in a familiar, also #arousing way. the first friend who read a draft thought the writing was good but was so upset and disgusted by it there were parts she couldn't read. overall, she hated it. i put it away for nearly a year after, until i started to realize that such a #passionate response surely meant something that i should investigate further, despite the it being painful. glad i finished it. i hope you will be too... "#feminist in its worldmaking, #intellectual in its #erotic #poetry, and razor sharp in its depictions of contemporary american gender ideology, kimberly dark's the daddies is a complex and genre-bending contribution to the archive of #queer feeling and to theorizing through #storytelling. in this autoethnography of daddy's worlds, the girls who inhabit and work in them are allowed to examine pleasures and pains of power and contradiction. taking a range of positions, dark's writing dares to interrogate the #psychic structures and deep ambivalences of a queer desire and kinship form in ways that move us beyond simplistic ideas of perversion and subversion. the daddies is a welcome addition to fem(me)inist sexual theory and a portrait of contemporary patriarchy by and for daddy's girls, by and author who has lived and survived and dared to tell. plus we learn more about what is at the root of #metoo and its perpetual reproductions from this book than many other contemporary sources. - ulrika dahl professor of gender studies at uppsala university, co-author of femmes of power: exploding queer femininities (hashtags are mine) @brillpublishing

text: a student asked libby larsen in masterclass, "what has changed for women composers over the course of your career, and what challenges do they still face?" after watching her with such energy and enthusiasm for two hours, suddenly she began and cut off a few thoughts, then explained, "you see, i'm stammering now because this makes me very angry and i have a lot to say." to paraphrase, she answered, "direct rejection is no longer acceptable. when i was a graduate student, you could say, 'you can't do this because you're woman.' you can't do that anymore. now we have things like the #metoo movement which show you how long things have been going on and how they are still. but apart from that, not much has changed. women composers still face marginalization and benign negligence. i was taught to keep asking direct questions until you get answers, sit in the road and refuse to move, wear black and stand tall, and don't play games. let your brilliance and your talent show." #composertales #shewritesmusic #womenwritemusic #womencomposers

last yearтАЩs #metoo movement was not just a voice for sexual harassment, it also began to help shed light onto the issue of adult bullying, a real problem! one studying showing that 31% had experienced bullying themselves and 45% felt that it was becoming more accepted. which is a scary number considering the impact it can leave on someoneтАЩs life & health. 
not just in the moment but long term effects such as, sleep loss, anxiety, depression, $$ lost to sick days, stress from the bullying causing muscle pain, thyroid issues, high blood pressure, mood disorders, self harming and eating disorders. 
a study done by the american journal of public health issued in 2015 showed that victims of workplace bullying have double the risk of suicidal ideation of the subsequent 5 years! 
we may think of bullying and think kids, teenagers... and yes! that is very true, itтАЩs an on going war we fight for our children. 
but itтАЩs also happening to moms and dads. itтАЩs a very serious problem one that because they are adults they may feel shame and embarrassment, causing them to not seek out the help they need. 
letтАЩs help put an end to any stigmas of adult bullying, take it seriously, and stand up against it!!! тАв

text:
u.s. actress #amberheard, a star of the upcoming "aquaman" superhero movie and a u.n. human rights champion, said on monday her childhood in texas near the mexican border helped spark her activism.
"going home in his pickup truck, there was an "indelible impression left on my soul", a recognition of injustice and unfairness for children on the mexican side."
"simply due to where i was born, a few miles north of this line, i was free to travel back and forth as i saw fit," she told an audience at the united nations in geneva on monday. "thousands of others would risk everything "for a mere shot and an opportunity to have that which i was just awarded due to this accidental luck of my birth on the other side. that was when i first started to pick up on the sensation."
"social media now gives everybody the chance to change things, with online campaigns like #metoo, time's up, and black lives matter, and while hollywood had a responsibility to lead, it had failed to do so, she said."
"there is a certain amount of irony in the sense that hollywood is often held up as some sort of bastion of progressive ideals, yet is actually in reality the exact opposite." "on some of the most basic rights that we are starting, thank goodness, to take for granted in other disciplines, in other businesses, whether it is inclusion, pay equality, representation, diversity, you name it, we fall way behind." @amberheard ЁЯСПЁЯСП @channelnewsasia #humanrights  #standup4humanrights #sams #syrianrefugees #lgbtqi #lgbtqirights #unitednations #unitednationshumanrights #rightsandactivism #storytelling #librarytalks #unoglibrary  #ambassador #actress #activist #mera #aquaman #dceu #superhero #dccfans #dccfilms #dccmovies #dccomics #geneva

text: on the latest episode of the lunch table podcast, the table gets a surprise visit from star basketball player, maurice watson jr. having led creighton to the number 7 rank in the ncaa with a 17-1 record, maurice tragically tore his acl in the 19th game of his final collegiate season. from there, it all went south for maurice as he suddenly found himself being accused of sexually assaulting a fellow student at creighton. we explore maurice's trials and tribulations during his return from injury, falsified sexual assault accusations, and countless other set backs. maurice provides us insight into the raw details of his rough upbringing in philly, his split collegiate basketball career at both boston university and creighton, his road to recovery, and his painful and eye-opening experiences dealing with the us justice system during the apex of the #metoo movement. maurice highlights the importance of concrete friendships, his family, and an unwavering faith in god. he is now playing professional basketball in the fiba europe cup league and still maintains his childhood dream of playing in the nba. the maurice watson story has only been told to the lunch table podcast, so tune in for this rollercoaster ride of emotions! (episode link in the bio) @jaygillythekid @thelunchtablepc @gdiddy210 @mauricewatson10 @rawtruthradio

women have taken action against sexual assault by joining movements such as #metoo. this lecture presented by jennifer thomas, wilkes associate professor of psychology, examines why some women take action while others do not and how factors may influence a feminist identity.таА

text:
love letter monday
тАв
i was anorexic for 15 years. then, one day, it dawned on me that in a world that profits off the insecurity, timidity, and voicelessness of women, not only had my self-hatred been programmed into me, but my loyalty to that programming was complicity. so, rejecting that ingrained self-hatred would be тАФ is тАФ a riotous act of revolution. as a woman, loving oneself is an act of feminism. it is change, embodied.
тАв
in a world that feeds and functions on our smallness, dare to be bold.
тАв
dare to love.
dare to speak.
dare to demand space.
dare to grow.
dare to lead.
тАв
woman by woman, body by body, this is how we rise.
тАв
it is time.
тАв
love, reema
тАв

text:
music composer anu malik has stepped down from the jury panel of singing reality show, indian idol, a statement from sony entertainment television read. malik has been accused of sexual harassment by multiple women amid┬аthe #metoo movement┬аraging across the country.

the television channelтАЩs statement says a replacement will be found for him who will join the other two judges on the show, vishal dadlani & neha kakkar. тАЬanu malik is no longer a part of indian idol jury panel. the show will continue its planned schedule & weтАЩll invite some of the biggest names in indian music as guests to join vishal & neha to judge extraordinary talent of indian idol season 10,тАЭ the statement read.

malik also shared a statement saying he is taking a break from the show. тАЬi, anu malik, have decided to take a break from indian idol as i am currently unable to focus on my work on the show. the channel has been kind to agree for the same. thank you,тАЭ malik said.

after singers sona mohapatra & shweta pandit accused malik of sexual harassment, two budding singers levelled similar allegations against him.

shweta had said in her post that she was just 15 when malik made her uncomfortable by asking to kiss him. тАЬhad to go back to my worst memory as a teenage girl today to write this & speak up тАУ its now or never. this is┬аmy #metoo┬а& have to warn young girls about #anumalik & let you know your #timesup @indiametoo. thank you @sonamohapatra for speaking up about him & supporting this,тАЭ she wrote on twitter.

earlier, in an instagram post, singer sona mahapatra wrote, тАЬto all the young girls & women who are coming out with their experiences with this creep, journalists, тАШfansтАЩ & even kids from college, know that you are not alone. this guy, #kailashkher is a serial predator & has been for years as are many others like anu malik in the industry. i cannot be tweeting about everyone cus i work 18 hour work days & have a life to live & breathe in.тАЭ sona had tweeted again on saturday saying by not taking action against malik, makers of the show are complicit.

a lawyer for the music director thursday denied the claims against him, saying┬аindiaтАЩs #metoo movement is being used for his clientтАЩs

text:
dear men,
from a very young age i was taught that i should speak softly, be polite, submissive, etc. etc. you basically want me to be, how you so politely put it, accommodating.

you think i am so weak that it's become your 'thing' to insinuate that i am the one who is okay with this present trend of rape culture. 
someone said that i am like "fresh meat". and when said "fresh meat" is left in the open, the dogs are tempted to have it. you say that this is why one should keep the said "meat" inside the house. but what if i say that you should tie up your dogs? that's a better idea, isn't it?

you think that i am the one who provokes you to rape me by just walking on the streets at 9 p.m. but don't you think that it's kind of embarrassing that you are turned on just by the idea of me walking? i mean dude, ever heard of self control?  and then you say i'm desperate.

you parade about with the agenda of "disciplining" me by raping me and saying that you're doing me a favour.  what if i start doing the same? what if the next time i see you walking around the streets at 9 p.m. and decide that you need to be taught a lesson? 
my idea sounds cringy. even barbaric. right? it sounds the same when you say it. 
i want this to be a message to all of you out there. i accept who i am and i don't give a single flying fuck about what you think.

so yeah, i am not sorry that i'm a girl.
from, 
a female human ┬й mysticЁЯНБ

text:
hereтАЩs one about #mentalhealth- 
when i think about my #depression, i think about this photo. this girl had just been told that she was тАЬnot fun to be around,тАЭ that тАЬno one wanted to spend time with herтАЭ and that a man especially would only put up with being around her тАЬfor one thing.тАЭ she was manipulated, she was verbally, mentally and emotionally abused. she was pushed and pulled and blamed and sometimes loved and worshipped as though nothing bad had happened. when this photo was taken, she was completely broken, has lost a staggering amount of weight from stress and didnтАЩt recognize herself. somehow, in some moment coerced by nicole, this genuine smile happened. iтАЩm pretty certain it was a hysterical laugh at my situation, but i like to see it as a glimmer of hope. i see myself as truly beautiful because it shows the spark that i still had within me. a spark which, though i did go back to this man only weeks later, allowed me to finally stand up for myself. 
itтАЩs been years. my confidence is still shaken. i still doubt that anyone ever genuinely wants to spend time with me, but each day i get better. 
most of my followers know this man. several of them shared that wonderful тАЬif i am friends with your abuser, let me know and i will unfriend themтАЭ post that was going around. i somehow only found the strength to say his name to one of them. the rest continue to praise him, unknowing. 
sharing today to praise the other women who have #stoodup, said #timesup and #metoo and victims of #abusiverelationships including #mentalabuse #emotionalabuse and #sexualabuse. remember: check on your strong friends. find your glimmer of #hope and hold on. 
photo credit: @shesophoto

text:
on the latest episode of the lunch table podcast, the table gets a surprise visit from star basketball player, @mauricewatson10. having led @bluejaymbb to the number 7 rank in the @ncaasports with a 17-1 record, maurice tragically tore his acl in the 19th game of his final collegiate season. from there, it all went south for maurice as he suddenly found himself being accused of sexually assaulting a fellow student at #creighton. we explore maurice's trials and tribulations during his return from injury, falsified sexual assault accusations, and countless other set backs. maurice provides us insight into the raw details of his rough upbringing in #philadelphia, his split collegiate basketball career at both @bostonu and creighton, his road to recovery, and his painful and eye-opening experiences dealing with the #us justice system during the apex of the #metoo movement. maurice highlights the importance of concrete friendships, his family, and an unwavering faith in #god. he is now playing professional #basketball in the #fiba europe cup league and still maintains his childhood dream of playing in the @nba. the maurice watson story has only been told to the lunch table podcast, so tune in for this rollercoaster ride of emotions! (episode link in the bio)

text:
darling, you feel heavy because you are too full of truth. open your mouth more and let the truth exist somewhere other than inside your body. - della hicks-wilson
.
this weekend at the @theuncommonwoman live event shook me from head to toe.
.
standing up sharing my story released a powerful vibration within me. knowing that i am walking my truth and reality i create everyday.
.
every speaker and every word they spoke left a mark with each of us so powerful and healing. this weekend was truly magic. all together as uncommon women & men.
.
i am so full of gratitude and love for this experience and each connection made this weekend. this movement is like no other. i am so blessed to be a part of it and to be witness to it. .
incredibly blessed to have the amazing support and love crom@my family as they have witnessed and supported me during my journey. no words to express my full love for all this.
.
i am so looking toward to the future, sharing more. standing in stages more and impacting more. my path never been so clear as what i need to do next. my passion to inspire others like me to have the #pwr2change.
.
.
.

text_retweet:
today i release all resistence of the past and move into the present moment

often times we are hunted by the mistakes we have made in our past. we live in bondage to our past pain, traumas and actions that we are not proud of.

we have believed the lie that we must be perfect without flaws for so long that we have no idea that human perfection is an illusion.

we are spiritual beings having an human experience to expand in conciousness. soul expansion evolves from conquering our problems, overcoming our fears and growing from lessons learned. 
i call the тАЬdevilтАЭ those self-defeating behaviors and thoughts that cause us to hold ourselves in bondage to lack of self love and resistence to change. what we resist persist.

fear is the greatest devil of them all. it is usually fear that causes guilt and shame. 
we are afraid of what people will think of us if they knew this flaw. fear of what could happen if i made this change in my life. fear of what could go wrong or who will be disappointed.

we must stop worrying about what others think about us & our lives and focus more on failing ourselves if we donтАЩt live the life we know we desire deep down inside.

the only way to begin to live that life is to break the chains of the past and move forward into our future with no regrets and know that the things that happened to us or the mistakes we made in the past is what propels us into greatness and thru our tests emerges our testimony to inspire others.

take the lesson as a blessing and move forward in gratitude for growth.

stop holding on to what is hindering and gravitate towards what will honor our highest and greatest self.

this is the realization the main character monee had to come to grips with in the book i wrote, тАЬthe devils bedroom.тАЭ the main charcter monee, had to discover that self love is self acceptance тАУ all of it тАУ the good and the bad.

in order to healтАж the chains of guilt and shame must be broken with self love and forgiveness.

today i release all resistence of the past and move into the present moment

i just won the season 7 of all india corporate talent championship for solo dance тЭдтЭдso happy. the competition was judged by @marzipestonji and @anushkadisco and their comments for my performance were truly humbling. i am glad i could do justice to this theme that i chose. 
with the #metoo movement, i wanted to bring to notice, the sexual harassment of men. why do we ridicule a man who is sexually harassed. we ridicule him more if he is violated by a woman. is it correct to question his masculinity?
this is the story of one such guy who is violated by a family member (gender of the offender is not revealed) the guy tries to resist and tell it to people, but he is threatened and ridiculed and muted by social pressure to meet his fateful judgement. 
i hope you like the performance and take harassment of men as seriously as that of women. 
let's not make this a battle of genders, it is never us vs them, we have enough discrimination, let's support each other for what is right. you're not alone..it is  #youandmetoo тЭд
thanks to all the participants who supported me so much. i really appreciate it тЭдтЭд
thanks for the video @deshreyas

text:
review of тАЬbernhardt/hamletтАЭ part 2 of 2.
.
rebeckтАЩs bernhardt is a complex creature. she has ego, ambition, and gravitas, but she also has immense fear of failure and self-doubt. she enjoys fame, praise, and admiration yet demands respect, privacy, and discretion. she may be a woman but she is not submissive. she may be beautiful but she is not delicate. she may be an actress but she is not stupid. bernhardt is aware of her power and presence and she knows exactly what to do with them.
.
the dazzling janet mcteer is captivating as bernhardt. she is sensual, playful, and magnetic. mcteerтАЩs real power isnтАЩt fully harnessed until act two, but it is worth the wait. in bernhardtтАЩs confrontation scene with her lover, playwright edmond rostand (cleverly played by jason butler harner), i swear, mcteer stopped the room. no one moved or made a sound until she took one last disappointed, broken hearted look at rostand and closed the door behind her.
.
this play has much to offer a 21st century audience. you donтАЩt need to know anything about bernhardt, shakespeare, or 19th century france to enjoy it or to get something out of it. it may not be the sexiest or the easiest play on #broadway right now, but i suppose that depends on your perspective and your willingness. but in the age of #metoo, #womensreality, and #nastywoman, who wouldnтАЩt want to see a play about a woman who stands up for herself and fights for what she wants; a woman who does things her own way and refuses to back down just because a man tells her тАЬno.тАЭ
.
#theresarebek #bernhardthamlet #janetmcteer #roundabouttheatre #broadway #theater #theatre

text:
hey guys. 
so, @ronnyonkeo & i are thinking of creating a scream platform, and we need your voices.
do you want to share your personal stories about any form of sexual harassment, from the mildest incidents to the harshest? 
we want to hear you. 
any story really, even one of you defending yourself, or someone else defending you. 
this is your platform. we are slowly building it, stone by stone. for you. for all of us. 
if you so wish, your identity will remain purely hidden. 
we want your stories, we want to tell them to the world, show them that this is happening & we need to stop it. 
inbox me if you're interested in this, any part of it, really. 
even with tips & whatnot. 
also, my dm is still a safe space, and my house will be a home for you. if you need to just talk, we can drink coffee or whiskey or just plain water, i'll be here, to listen, and to help. 
#scream
#enough
#metoo

text:
survivors of childhood sexual abuse hide their emotions from the world to protect themselves from being labeled, stigmatized or judge about the things that happened to them as children. i remember wearing a different mask every day just to fit in with the world. but when i returned home after a long day of acting behind a mask i would again become that wounded little child. i would curl up in a ball and cry myself to sleep every night. every day i struggled to hide the things that were destroying me inside from my childhood. today i choose to no longer hide my feelings or put on a mask to fit in or to be part of the world. if the world accepts me for who i am or not is not my concern anymore. i have to live my truth no matter what happens. no more masks. no more silence.  i am me raw, authentic and a survivor.

cecibel contreras
isuvoa.com

text:
thrilled to have lara bundock present on the panel after our film screening. please join us at the broadway theater in nottingham england on october 30th for this special screening.
lara bundock is the founding ceo of тАШthe snowdrop projectтАЩ. after training as a social worker, she practiced in an nrm safe house and was shocked by the lack of available support after the nrm. seeing previous clients become homeless, develop debt, drug and alcohol problems or become missing people; she designed a social work based support programme to address clients ongoing needs. the project grew to include counselling, community activities, a house renovation service and pathways to education/employment. lara co-authored тАШlife beyond the safe houseтАЩ (2015) and has spoken around the uk, northern ireland and turkmenistan about working with survivors of trafficking. she is passionate about needs-led support being available nationwide following methods of best practice and equipping others to understand the complex needs of survivors.
